me.lucko.helper.messaging.bungee

Class BungeeMessaging

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.lucko.helper.messaging.bungee.BungeeMessaging
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PluginMessageListener

    @NonnullByDefault
public final class BungeeMessaging
extends Object
implements PluginMessageListener
    Wrapper class for the BungeeCord Plugin Messaging API, providing callbacks to read response data

    See: https://www.spigotmc.org/wiki/bukkit-bungee-plugin-messaging-channel and https://github.com/SpigotMC/BungeeCord/blob/master/proxy/src/main/java/net/md_5/bungee/connection/DownstreamBridge.java#L223

      • forward

        public static void forward(String serverName,
                           String channelName,
                           byte[] data)
        Sends a custom plugin message to a given server.

        You can use registerForwardCallbackRaw(String, Predicate) to register listeners on a given subchannel.

        Parameters:
        serverName - the name of the server to send to. use ALL_SERVERS to send to all servers, or ONLINE_SERVERS to only send to servers which are online.
        channelName - the name of the subchannel
        data - the data to send

      • registerForwardCallbackRaw

        public static void registerForwardCallbackRaw(String channelName,
                                              Predicate<byte[]> callback)
        Registers a callback to listen for messages sent on forwarded subchannels.

        Use forward(String, String, byte[]) to dispatch messages.

        Parameters:
        channelName - the name of the channel to listen on
        callback - the callback. the predicate should return true when the callback should be unregistered.

      • registerForwardCallback

        public static void registerForwardCallback(String channelName,
                                           Predicate<ByteArrayDataInput> callback)
        Registers a callback to listen for messages sent on forwarded subchannels.

        Use forward(String, String, ByteArrayDataOutput) to dispatch messages.

        Parameters:
        channelName - the name of the channel to listen on
        callback - the callback. the predicate should return true when the callback should be unregistered.
